## Arch Review — 2026-03-15

**Codebase health: good.** Build, clippy, and all 914 tests pass clean.

---

### One new finding filed

**`red-cell-c2-k00o` (P2 — Security/OPSEC) — Codex**
`teamserver/src/listeners.rs:927` — `fake_404_response()` unconditionally injects an `x-havoc: true` response header into every non-matching HTTP request (wrong method, URI, user-agent, unknown agent, etc.). Any network scanner can fingerprint a live Red Cell listener with a single HTTP probe. Fix: remove the header, or make it opt-in via the listener profile.

